<% content_for :title do %>Admin overview | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>Workspace administration in <%= installation_brand_name %>: account settings, agents, inboxes, audit logs, and billing.<% end %>

<h1>Admin overview</h1>
<p class="lead">
  Workspace <strong>administrators</strong> configure <%= installation_brand_name %> for the whole organization.
  The first user in a new workspace is usually an admin.
</p>

<h2>Settings menu map</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Account settings</strong> — workspace name, locale, domain, features</li>
  <li><strong>Agents</strong> — invite users, roles, availability</li>
  <li><strong>Teams</strong> — agent groups — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('teams-labels') %>">Teams & labels guide</a></li>
  <li><strong>Agent assignment</strong> — round-robin, capacity (if enabled)</li>
  <li><strong>Inboxes</strong> — all channel connections — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('channels') %>">Channels overview</a></li>
  <li><strong>Labels</strong> — conversation tags</li>
  <li><strong>Custom attributes</strong> — extra fields on contacts, companies, conversations</li>
  <li><strong>Automation</strong> — event rules — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('automations-bots') %>">Automations guide</a></li>
  <li><strong>Agent bots</strong> — webhook bots</li>
  <li><strong>Macros</strong> — multi-step agent actions</li>
  <li><strong>Canned responses</strong> — reply snippets</li>
  <li><strong>Integrations</strong> — Slack, webhooks, apps — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('integrations') %>">Integrations guide</a></li>
  <li><strong>Audit logs</strong> — who changed what</li>
  <li><strong>Custom roles</strong> — fine-grained permissions — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('security-roles') %>">Security & roles</a></li>
  <li><strong>SLA</strong> — response time policies — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('sla-workflow') %>">SLA & workflow</a></li>
  <li><strong>Conversation workflow</strong> — resolve rules, auto-assignment</li>
  <li><strong>Security</strong> — MFA, session policies</li>
  <li><strong>Billing</strong> — plan and usage (cloud / hosted installs)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Account settings</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Workspace name and locale</li>
  <li><strong>Custom domain</strong> — inbound email reply domain (requires DNS; see <a href="<%= guide_page_path('channel-email') %>">Email channels</a>)</li>
  <li><strong>Support email</strong> — custom sender address for conversation emails</li>
  <li>Auto-resolve duration (optional)</li>
</ul>
<p>All plans include the same features; billing limits agent seats and monthly Copilot usage. See <a href="<%= pricing_path %>">Pricing</a>.</p>

<h2>Manage agents</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Settings → Agents → Add agent</strong></li>
  <li>Enter email; user receives invite</li>
  <li>Role: <strong>Administrator</strong> or <strong>Agent</strong></li>
  <li>Custom roles override defaults when configured</li>
  <li>Set agent availability (online / busy / offline) from profile</li>
</ol>

<h2>Manage inboxes</h2>
<p>See <a href="<%= guide_page_path('channels') %>">Channels overview</a> for every channel type. After creating an inbox, always add collaborators and test inbound/outbound messages.</p>

<h2><%= installation_captain_name %> (AI)</h2>
<p>Configured from the <strong><%= installation_captain_name %></strong> sidebar: assistants, documents, FAQs, scenarios, tools, and inbox connections. See the <a href="<%= guide_page_path('captain') %>"><%= installation_captain_name %> guide</a> for setup steps and how auto-reply works on WhatsApp and other channels.</p>

<h2>Help Center (your customers’ docs)</h2>
<p>Separate from this User Guide. Your workspace can publish a public KB at <code>/hc/your-slug</code>. See <a href="<%= guide_page_path('help-center') %>">Help Center guide</a>.</p>

<h2>Audit logs</h2>
<p>Review agent actions: settings changes, conversation exports, login events. Useful for compliance and debugging permission issues.</p>

<h2>Billing</h2>
<p>On <%= installation_brand_name %>, <strong>Settings → Billing</strong> shows your plan (Starter, Growth, or Business), agent seat usage, Copilot allowance, and Pesapal payment history. Upgrade to add more agents; all plans include the same product features.</p>

<h2>Admin onboarding checklist</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Complete account settings and timezone</li>
  <li>Invite agents and create teams</li>
  <li>Connect at least one inbox and test</li>
  <li>Create labels and canned responses</li>
  <li>Configure SLA and workflow if needed</li>
  <li>Enable integrations (Slack, etc.)</li>
  <li>Set up <%= installation_captain_name %> or bots if using automation</li>
  <li>Publish Help Center articles for end customers (optional)</li>
</ol>

<div class="cta-box">
  <p><strong>New workspace?</strong> Start with <a href="<%= guide_page_path('workspace-setup') %>">Workspace setup</a>.</p>
</div>
